{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"O(n) balanced bulk build from sorted array","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"ef763ba6535b75e53fbf8c2236ef28f4f852a6d491b4ba9fc1d50efcd275f620","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:40:09Z","created_by":"Jordan Baker","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Node.fromIntervals() currently sorts then inserts one-by-one (O(n log n)). Since we have sorted intervals, we can build a balanced AVL tree bottom-up in O(n) by recursively splitting the sorted array at the midpoint. This would speed up tree construction and mergeOverlaps() which rebuilds from scratch.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"intervaltree-0rq","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"jbb@scryent.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Bulk build fromIntervals() in O(n) instead of O(n log n)","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"O(1) size counter with insert/remove tracking","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:51Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"2fb174a276e81b582477eb7834021478e21c3bb5e3ff18ceb6d2abd5ba2e1e82","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:40:09Z","created_by":"Jordan Baker","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"tree.size currently calls toArray().length which is O(n). Focuster checks .size and .isEmpty frequently. Should increment/decrement a counter on insert/remove for O(1) access. Also makes isEmpty trivially O(1).","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"intervaltree-2v6","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"jbb@scryent.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Maintain size as a running counter instead of toArray().length","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:51Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"shared module-level scratch arrays for insert flags","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"9e9a01f3cd98f05d3c0859239259e7d4d7ec70127e2f6b6f16f69306440d25b0","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:40:09Z","created_by":"Jordan Baker","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Node.insert() allocates two [boolean] arrays (rebalancingDone, updateRequired) on every call for communicating state up the recursion. These heap allocations are unnecessary — consider using a class-level field or return value encoding instead.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"intervaltree-9wc","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"jbb@scryent.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":3,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Optimize insert() — avoid allocating [boolean] flag arrays","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"first()/last() O(log n) via min()/max() tree walk","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:51Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"9b2ac5992cde83b111ce3943a768bd88fb0e570193889cf242657889f69d35e6","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:40:09Z","created_by":"Jordan Baker","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Focuster does tree.toSorted()[0] and tree.toArray()[tree.size-1] to get first/last intervals — both O(n) since they flatten the entire tree. AVL trees support O(log n) min/max by walking left/right branches. Add first() and last() methods that return the min-start and max-start intervals without materializing the full array.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"intervaltree-anm","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"jbb@scryent.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Add first()/last() methods for O(log n) min/max access","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:51Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"updateAttributes() optimized with for-loops, 5.2x improvement","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:48Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"9ddae98db787ea3786b4afd2b50ab1ab7ae6c3f92db215997a62f382ffc9f272","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:40:09Z","created_by":"Jordan Baker","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Node.updateAttributes() uses Math.min(...this.values.map(iv =\u003e iv.start)) and similar patterns with spread. This allocates intermediate arrays and spreads them on every insert and rotation — it's the hottest inner loop in the tree. Replace with simple for-loops over this.values + direct child property access.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"intervaltree-e1l","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"jbb@scryent.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Optimize updateAttributes() — eliminate spread + map allocations","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:48Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"dirty flag skips redundant mergeOverlaps, 3.2x improvement","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"ecf58ac3a15b87d79c9e35c03f05f41d1edbe21028c889f7849dfb704d7b770f","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:40:09Z","created_by":"Jordan Baker","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Focuster calls mergeOverlaps() before every searchByLengthStartingAt() in the schedule loop (~100 times). mergeOverlaps() rebuilds the entire tree from scratch. If the tree hasn't been modified since the last merge, this is pure waste. Add a dirty flag that's set on add/remove/chop and cleared on merge, allowing no-op merges.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"intervaltree-e5c","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"jbb@scryent.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Add dirty flag to skip redundant mergeOverlaps()","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"chop simplified to single searchOverlap","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"8c53518bab3d6b3b6d4aaa1e682027954dced72ca2ac584e0be512ebccd29d7c","created_at":"2026-03-27T04:40:09Z","created_by":"Jordan Baker","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"chop(start, end) currently does: 2x searchPoint + removeEnveloped (which does searchOverlap + filter + N removes) + removeAll + addAll. For Focuster's workload this is called 100+ times during initialization. Consider a single-pass approach that walks the tree once, collecting what to remove and what to insert, then rebuilds.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"intervaltree-oiv","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"jbb@scryent.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Optimize chop() — reduce from 5 tree operations to fewer","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:21:50Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
